document_data.Notable Kukalatu:
*[[Apimu]], an extremely skilled and extremely neurotic [[garudaskin]] crafter in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Sharp Teeth, Mostly Tasty‎‎|7}}
*[[Bifu]], meaning "Big Foot", was a tough and valorous hunter in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Gihu]], or "Agile Hands", a mischievous rogue in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Sharp Teeth, Mostly Tasty‎‎|5}}
*[[eJahi]], or "Open Welcome", a warrior of the tribe who liked attention and appreciated revelry, active in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[eNuka Ximi]], an old and toothless village traded and cook who could rant about not having human meat endlessly in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[eVuku Piki]], or "SheVery Smart,Peaceful Wisdom", a wise elder of the Council of Almost Ancestors in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Nuaki Latu]], a jovial hunter of the tribe in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Sharp Teeth, Mostly Tasty‎‎|4}}
*[[Nuta Vimu]], or "Not Fast, Fat Belly", a member of the Council of Almost Ancestors in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite organized play/LJ/Sharp Teeth, Mostly Tasty‎‎|6}}
*[[Wisu Jiju]], "Wind Sound, Strong Spell", a powerful wizard of the tribe and one of the councilmen in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
